events.title: Travel Authorization Approved for Witness Interviews
events.description: Travel authorization 10893150 received final approval for a traveler named 'Minor' to travel to the United States for witness interviews related to U.S. v. Epstein.

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID: 10893150) was approved on December 13, 2019, for a traveler identified only as 'Minor'.
The purpose of the travel was for witness interviews related to the federal case 'U.S. v. Epstein'.
The authorization was processed through the U.S. Department of Justice's E2 travel system.
The destination was the United States, specifically associated with the New York Southern district office.
The document is an automated notification email, indicating formal DOJ travel procedures were being followed for case-related witness coordination.
